icProfile?language=EN>Zeldagis Ravensoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 7:42:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1427.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Why petition?</span><hr size=1> I've got a question.  After the thread by Bumbum, I began wondering... would you petition someone for their name?  Honestly, there's no way I would, then again, I consider it a waste of time to petition people at all.    Be it KS'ing, training, or vulgarities, I just don't see myself ever bothering.  I'm more of a &quot;I don't get mad, I get even&quot; kind of guy.  <br>
<br>
Really, as far as behavior goes, the only thing I think should be petitionable would be harassment or threats.  I would never personally petition or report for either one (I've got thick skin, and I usually don't give a shit what people say or think), but I understand why someone would need to.<br>
<br>
So I guess the question is, where do you draw your petition line?<br>
<br>
Zel<br>
<br>
P.S. Yes, I realize if everyone were like me there would be no petitions, but then again, it's not as if your petitions are ever answered in a timely manner. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 963<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/19/02 7:51:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1427.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why petition?</span><hr size=1> I petitioned an erudite named &quot;Iamblack&quot;<br>
<br>
I think I may have petitioned &quot;Cyberstoner&quot; although I'm not sure about that one.<br>
<br>
Mostly I just snicker about these names and send tells to all my friends so we can make fun of them together.<br>
<br>
Generally I think you're right about petitioning...it's barely helped me any.  Usually by the time they are answered the offending event transpired hours ago.  I did get some pretty fast help after someone tried repeatedly to train me, then tried to KS me, and then sent me tells threatening to kill me IRL.<br>
<br>
Basically I don't have any set guildlines.  Generally if something gets me really upset, I'll petition.  The last petition I submitted was when a surnamed character was training a number of us young halflings in Misty Thickets with mobs that were yellow to me at level 2, but I had no chance of surviving.  Somewhere about 15 mobs at a time.  He wasn't just ruining my fun, but also everyone elses, and we petitioned together.  I rerolled shortly after that.<br>
